Three programming paradigms (styles):

1. Imperative: based on the “turing machine”
2. Object oriented : based on the “turing machine”
3. Functional, and : based on “lambda calculus”
4. Declarative paradigm: based on “first order logic”

Detail Of Above in the followig link
https://medium.com/functional-javascript/introduction-to-functional-javascript-45a9dca6c64a

1. First Class Functions
*****

```
function greet(name) { 
 console.log('Hello ' + name) 
}greet(“John”) // “Hello John”var sayHello = greet 
sayHello(“Alex”) // “Hello Alex”
